The input parameter `flowers` is a 2D array representing the times when the flowers are in full bloom.
The input parameter `persons` is an array representing the times when the people arrive.
The length of `flowers` is equal to the number of flowers.
The length of `persons` is equal to the number of people.
The elements in `flowers` and `persons` are non-negative integers.
The elements in `flowers` and `persons` are sorted in ascending order.
